    "problemStatement": "Number of inversion\n\nWrite a program to count the number of inversion in a given array.\n\nTwo element a[i] and a[j] form an inversion ifa[i] > a[j] and i <j. For simplicity, we may assume that all elements are unique.\n\nExpected Output :\n\nThe given array is : 1 9 6 4 5\n\nThe inversions are: (9, 6) (9, 4) (9, 5) (6, 4) (6, 5)\n\nThe number of inversion can be formed from the array is: 5",
    "constraints": [
      "1 <= N <= 50",
      "1 <= arr[i] <= 1000"
    ],
    "inputFormat": "The input contains the number of elements and the values",
    "outputFormat": "Check sample output",
